  abstract={Objective: To investigate the influence of character strengths on adolescent depressive symptoms and regulatory effect of gender and age. Methods: From April to July in 2011, using VIA-Youth and CES-D, we conducted measurement of character strengths and depression level on 70 628 adolescents enrolled from 10 sample provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the administration of central government (Beijing, Shanghai, Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Guangdong, Fujian, Chongqing, Guangxi, Inner Mongolia and Anhui) and one sample city (Shijiazhuang). The number of effective subjects was 47 872. The regulatory effect of gender and age on the relationship between character strengths and adolescent depression symptoms was investigated using multi-level multivariate linear regression analysis. Results: The score of character strengths of adolescents was (719.31 ± 84.06), and the score of depression symptom was (14.64 ± 10.08). The score of depression symptom and age had positive correlation (r =0.097, P <0.001), while gender and character strengths had negative correlation (r values were -0.026 and -0.489; P < 0.001). character strengths had a backward prediction of depression symptom (β =-0.495, P <0.001). Gender had no regulatory effect on the relationship between character strengths and depression symptom (β =-0.007, P =0.095). Age had regulatory effect on the relationship between character strengths and depression symptom (β =-0.056, P <0.001). Conclusion: Character strengths alleviates depression of adolescents, and its effect is more obvious among adolescents with higher age. Copyright © 2016 by the Chinese General Practice.},
